1
00:00:00,566 --> 00:00:04,533
(Episode 7: Yu Jun, We Won First Place)

2
00:00:05,566 --> 00:00:08,400
(Five minute before pre-recording)

3
00:00:10,166 --> 00:00:15,566
(We have to make him stop crying
before getting on stage.)

4
00:00:19,466 --> 00:00:21,000
Were you upset, Yu Jun?

5
00:00:23,833 --> 00:00:25,066
You feel comfortable in my arms, right?

6
00:00:25,784 --> 00:00:27,700
You've always liked it.

7
00:00:27,700 --> 00:00:29,500
(Thankfully, Yu Jun stops crying.)

8
00:00:32,100 --> 00:00:33,200
(Quiet)

9
00:00:33,200 --> 00:00:35,266
(Calm)

10
00:00:35,266 --> 00:00:38,633
(I won't let this go.)

11
00:00:39,100 --> 00:00:39,933
BEOMGYU.

12
00:00:40,900 --> 00:00:45,500
(Putting on name tags
before going on stage)

13
00:00:45,700 --> 00:00:47,733
YEONJUN, let me put your name tag on you
before you go.

14
00:00:48,200 --> 00:00:49,266
How do I wear that?

15
00:00:49,266 --> 00:00:51,066
He can wear it when he comes back down.

16
00:00:51,066 --> 00:00:54,466
(He gives up on wearing a name tag
so Yu Jun doesn't cry.)

17
00:00:55,433 --> 00:00:56,500
Should we do it as the ending pose?

18
00:00:56,500 --> 00:00:58,466
Should we do a pose for Yu Jun?

19
00:00:58,466 --> 00:01:00,233
- That sounds good.
- Let's make a big heart.

20
00:01:00,233 --> 00:01:01,133
A big heart like this.
"I love you."

21
00:01:02,033 --> 00:01:03,900
Let's make a heart gesture at the end.

22
00:01:03,900 --> 00:01:05,166
Yu Jun, shall we do "I love you?"

23
00:01:05,166 --> 00:01:06,000
I love you.

24
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:07,566
(They'll do Yu Jun's "I love you" pose.)

25
00:01:08,333 --> 00:01:09,333
I love you.

26
00:01:09,733 --> 00:01:12,433
(BEOMGYU gets Yu Jun's confirmation
for the ending pose.)

27
00:01:12,666 --> 00:01:15,266
- Good work.
- Good work.

28
00:01:15,266 --> 00:01:16,400
He's so cute.

29
00:01:16,400 --> 00:01:17,600
Hello.

30
00:01:18,409 --> 00:01:19,943
- How cute.
- Great work, Jae Hwan.

31
00:01:19,944 --> 00:01:21,099
(Great work, Uncle Senior.)

32
00:01:21,100 --> 00:01:25,033
(TOMORROW X TOGETHER's pre-recording time)

33
00:01:25,033 --> 00:01:26,477
- Please go on stage.
- Okay.

34
00:01:26,478 --> 00:01:28,088
(Yu Jun is going to the stage to say hi.)

35
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:32,166
(MOA, Yu Jun is here.)

36
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:35,533
(It's Yu Jun!)

37
00:01:35,533 --> 00:01:37,600
(Be quiet. You'll scare Yu Jun.)

38
00:01:38,233 --> 00:01:39,433
Yu Jun, say hello.

39
00:01:39,566 --> 00:01:40,466
(Bowing)

40
00:01:41,300 --> 00:01:43,233
(He's cute!)

41
00:01:43,233 --> 00:01:44,433
Isn't he adorable?

42
00:01:45,266 --> 00:01:45,966
He's adorable.

43
00:01:45,966 --> 00:01:47,100
(Amazed)

44
00:01:47,100 --> 00:01:48,700
Yu Jun, they're my girlfriends.

45
00:01:48,700 --> 00:01:51,800
(The girlfriends are in love with Yu Jun.)

46
00:01:52,166 --> 00:01:54,533
"Uncles, are you guys this popular?"

47
00:01:54,533 --> 00:01:56,666
(Yu Jun is confused
on the day of his debut.)

48
00:01:57,700 --> 00:01:59,266
(Winking)

49
00:02:00,800 --> 00:02:01,633
Hello.

50
00:02:02,133 --> 00:02:04,200
(A rookie must have a specialty.)

51
00:02:04,200 --> 00:02:05,566
Yu Jun, high-five.

52
00:02:05,566 --> 00:02:07,100
(Will he respond?)

53
00:02:07,100 --> 00:02:08,333
High-five. Okay.

54
00:02:08,600 --> 00:02:09,466
High-five.

55
00:02:10,433 --> 00:02:14,000
(I'll show you next time.)

56
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:17,233
We fed him breakfast this morning.

57
00:02:19,366 --> 00:02:20,933
He cried so much right before this.

58
00:02:21,166 --> 00:02:22,666
(That was a secret!)

59
00:02:23,466 --> 00:02:25,800
- Yu Jun, I love you.
- He's like a mozzarella stick.

60
00:02:25,800 --> 00:02:27,700
Hey, you're a mozzarella stick,
aren't you?

61
00:02:27,700 --> 00:02:31,733
(The uncles are busy showing off Yu Jun.)

62
00:02:31,733 --> 00:02:35,500
(It's time for a rehearsal.)

63
00:02:35,500 --> 00:02:38,100
(Sad)

64
00:02:38,100 --> 00:02:41,866
(Bowing again)

65
00:02:43,266 --> 00:02:44,500
Isn't he cute?

66
00:02:44,500 --> 00:02:46,133
(TOMORROW X TOGETHER and MOA
just love Yu Jun.)

67
00:02:46,133 --> 00:02:47,790
- Isn't he adorable?
- He is.

68
00:02:48,500 --> 00:02:50,633
(I don't want to go.)

69
00:02:50,633 --> 00:02:52,733
(Flustered)

70
00:02:52,733 --> 00:02:54,333
I'm going to go.

71
00:02:55,700 --> 00:02:59,100
(He cries as soon as YEONJUN lets him go.)

72
00:02:59,100 --> 00:03:00,066
I'm sorry.

73
00:03:02,300 --> 00:03:05,733
(But Uncles have to work.)

74
00:03:05,733 --> 00:03:07,100
(Worried)

75
00:03:07,100 --> 00:03:09,833
(The uncles feel bad for Yu Jun.)

76
00:03:09,833 --> 00:03:13,600
(The management team
will take care of Yu Jun.)

77
00:03:13,600 --> 00:03:16,866
(Going into work mode)

78
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:24,533
(We'll earn money for rice crackers!)

79
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:31,633
You cried so much, you'll nap like a rock.

80
00:03:33,400 --> 00:03:36,833
(The temporary uncle has a daughter
his age.)

81
00:03:37,266 --> 00:03:39,133
(Perfect weather for a walk)

82
00:03:39,800 --> 00:03:42,766
(Yu Jun is now calm and relaxed.)

83
00:03:43,233 --> 00:03:45,033
(Stomping)

84
00:03:45,500 --> 00:03:49,433
(It's nice to get some fresh air.)

85
00:03:49,866 --> 00:03:52,366
(Now he takes a waiting room tour
with his cart.)

86
00:03:52,666 --> 00:03:54,500
(Toddling)

87
00:03:55,533 --> 00:03:58,433
(The mozzarella stick legs
are working hard today.)

88
00:04:00,333 --> 00:04:03,433
(I'm not afraid of suitcases
bigger than me!)

89
00:04:04,100 --> 00:04:07,200
(Yu Jun is moving forward
without hesitation.)

90
00:04:07,200 --> 00:04:09,166
(It's cheese!)

91
00:04:09,166 --> 00:04:10,833
(Munching)

92
00:04:11,166 --> 00:04:14,133
(Snacking on cheese during the tour)

93
00:04:14,766 --> 00:04:16,300
(Munching)

94
00:04:16,300 --> 00:04:17,700
(Where should I go?)

95
00:04:18,933 --> 00:04:22,333
(Meanwhile, the uncles are working hard.)

96
00:04:23,466 --> 00:04:26,966
(And Yu Jun is watching them.)

97
00:04:28,366 --> 00:04:31,533
(Fully focused, completely still)

98
00:04:32,066 --> 00:04:35,366
(What is Yu Jun thinking about?
I'm just biting my lips.)

99
00:04:35,366 --> 00:04:39,800
(Staring)

100
00:04:40,300 --> 00:04:44,033
(Let me go keep pushing my cart.)

101
00:04:44,733 --> 00:04:45,566
Hi.

102
00:04:46,766 --> 00:04:48,366
(Meeting a stranger during the cart tour)

103
00:04:48,366 --> 00:04:50,666
(JEON MINWOOK of CLOSE YOUR EYES)

104
00:04:51,400 --> 00:04:54,400
(I keep going my own way.)

105
00:04:54,866 --> 00:04:57,833
(Might as well say hi since we met.)

106
00:04:57,833 --> 00:04:59,133
Nice to meet you.

107
00:04:59,400 --> 00:05:02,433
We're CLOSE YOUR EYES.

108
00:05:04,200 --> 00:05:05,633
(It's a toy!)

109
00:05:05,633 --> 00:05:06,466
Do you want it?

110
00:05:06,466 --> 00:05:08,866
(This keychain is mine now.)

111
00:05:09,500 --> 00:05:11,166
He's cute. Where are you going?

112
00:05:11,166 --> 00:05:12,733
(Running away with a extorted gift)

113
00:05:12,733 --> 00:05:15,033
(Hyped)

114
00:05:15,833 --> 00:05:19,933
(I'm a rebel cart racer, Choi Yu Jun.)

115
00:05:20,333 --> 00:05:21,300
(Sparkling)

116
00:05:21,300 --> 00:05:23,666
(What caught Yu Jun's eye?)

117
00:05:26,133 --> 00:05:30,233
(The uncles are doing the ending pose
they promised.)

118
00:05:30,466 --> 00:05:34,200
(I love you.)

119
00:05:34,200 --> 00:05:36,733
(Isn't that my signature heart?)

120
00:05:39,466 --> 00:05:42,566
(He sees it every day,
so he's not really interested.)

121
00:05:43,966 --> 00:05:46,733
(Yu Jun, I love you.)

122
00:05:48,933 --> 00:05:51,300
(Uncles, hold my hand.)

123
00:05:51,300 --> 00:05:52,200
He wants you to hold his hand.

124
00:05:52,200 --> 00:05:53,833
(I don't have my uncles to hold my hand.)

125
00:05:55,300 --> 00:05:57,333
(He meets other uncles
on his way to find his uncles.)

126
00:05:57,333 --> 00:05:59,133
(Jungsu and O.de of Xdinary Heroes)

127
00:05:59,133 --> 00:06:01,333
- You're a small creature.
- He's so cute.

128
00:06:01,333 --> 00:06:02,133
Where are you going?

129
00:06:02,133 --> 00:06:04,300
Where are you headed?

130
00:06:04,666 --> 00:06:07,300
Where are you going?

131
00:06:07,966 --> 00:06:11,133
(It's rare to see a baby pushing a cart
at the broadcasting station.)

132
00:06:11,133 --> 00:06:13,766
(Is the elevator here?)

133
00:06:14,600 --> 00:06:17,066
(Checking the elevator)

134
00:06:17,418 --> 00:06:19,066
(I'm taking this elevator, right?)

135
00:06:19,066 --> 00:06:20,833
He doesn't seem to know.

136
00:06:21,133 --> 00:06:24,700
(Let me go down and get my uncles.)

137
00:06:26,766 --> 00:06:29,500
What? You came to pick us up?

138
00:06:29,500 --> 00:06:31,066
Were you going to escape?

139
00:06:32,066 --> 00:06:32,933
Let's go.

140
00:06:32,933 --> 00:06:34,300
(Hold my hand.)

141
00:06:36,500 --> 00:06:38,300
(They ran into each other like fate.)

142
00:06:38,300 --> 00:06:39,366
What did you buy?

143
00:06:40,300 --> 00:06:42,533
(Now Yu Jun has someone
to hold his hand again.)

144
00:06:43,200 --> 00:06:45,066
(Hundred steps away
from their waiting room)

145
00:06:46,233 --> 00:06:47,300
Yu Jun, we're almost there.

146
00:06:47,566 --> 00:06:48,400
Speed up a little bit.

147
00:06:48,400 --> 00:06:49,966
We should pass by one more room.

148
00:06:49,966 --> 00:06:50,800
This is not it.

149
00:06:51,800 --> 00:06:53,866
(They finally arrived
at their waiting room at Yu Jun's pace.)

150
00:06:54,133 --> 00:06:54,900
Yu Jun.

151
00:06:55,566 --> 00:06:56,866
Why are you about to cry again?

152
00:06:57,300 --> 00:06:58,500
He's pouting.

153
00:06:59,400 --> 00:07:00,666
He's about to cry.

154
00:07:00,666 --> 00:07:01,466
Yu Jun, come here.

155
00:07:02,700 --> 00:07:06,833
(He's crying.)

156
00:07:08,366 --> 00:07:11,366
(For some reason, he's so upset.)

157
00:07:11,900 --> 00:07:14,166
What's wrong?
Should we give him a pacifier?

158
00:07:14,933 --> 00:07:15,766
Did he poop?

159
00:07:16,033 --> 00:07:16,866
Check.

160
00:07:16,866 --> 00:07:18,300
(Checking his diaper)

161
00:07:18,900 --> 00:07:20,933
(The idol singers are
in babysitting mode.)

162
00:07:21,133 --> 00:07:23,000
- He didn't poop. I think he peed.
- He peed.

163
00:07:24,400 --> 00:07:27,233
(After doing their job,
they catch up on parenting.)

164
00:07:28,933 --> 00:07:32,133
You peed.

165
00:07:32,133 --> 00:07:36,466
- Good boy.
- You held on for so long.

166
00:07:36,900 --> 00:07:38,833
- Good boy.
- Good job.

167
00:07:38,833 --> 00:07:41,733
(They quickly changed his diaper.)

168
00:07:41,900 --> 00:07:43,000
You're good at lip trills.

169
00:07:46,533 --> 00:07:47,633
Done!

170
00:07:47,633 --> 00:07:49,800
You're done.

171
00:07:50,966 --> 00:07:52,266
(Am I done?)

172
00:07:52,900 --> 00:07:54,700
(Applauding Yu Jun)

173
00:07:55,566 --> 00:07:58,133
(Now they're distracting Yu Jun
in every way possible.)

174
00:07:58,933 --> 00:08:02,766
(Shall we get snacks?)

175
00:08:03,500 --> 00:08:04,333
Let's go in.

176
00:08:04,333 --> 00:08:05,733
(I came to buy snacks with my cart.)

177
00:08:05,733 --> 00:08:08,666
(We came to take over
the convenience store!)

178
00:08:08,666 --> 00:08:10,733
Let's get ice cream first.

179
00:08:10,733 --> 00:08:12,066
Yu Jun, what do you want to eat?

180
00:08:12,366 --> 00:08:13,233
It looks good.

181
00:08:14,233 --> 00:08:15,833
What can Yu Jun eat?

182
00:08:15,833 --> 00:08:17,700
Can kids eat that?

183
00:08:17,700 --> 00:08:18,500
That cheese?

184
00:08:19,566 --> 00:08:22,766
(The 15-month-old baby, Yu Jun,
chooses his snack carefully.)

185
00:08:22,766 --> 00:08:24,366
Can he eat cream cheese?

186
00:08:25,466 --> 00:08:27,166
It does say it's for babies.

187
00:08:27,166 --> 00:08:28,566
- Is it for babies?
- Yes.

188
00:08:28,566 --> 00:08:30,000
Is it okay for him to eat cream cheese?

189
00:08:32,233 --> 00:08:33,700
I want the iced energy drink too.

190
00:08:34,433 --> 00:08:35,366
That sounds good.

191
00:08:36,133 --> 00:08:37,240
You're getting everything you want.

192
00:08:38,233 --> 00:08:40,700
(Done with convenience store shopping!)

193
00:08:40,700 --> 00:08:43,333
It's so funny how he follows the cart.

194
00:08:44,300 --> 00:08:47,833
- We can just leave him here.
- Yes. It's spacious here.

195
00:08:48,800 --> 00:08:49,966
Let's go! There you go.

196
00:08:49,966 --> 00:08:52,100
- Go to the rooftop and come back.
- Okay.

197
00:08:52,100 --> 00:08:54,166
You'll get back in time
for the live recording, then.

198
00:08:54,633 --> 00:08:55,766
You're doing well.

199
00:08:55,766 --> 00:08:56,733
(Walking up the wooden stairs)

200
00:08:56,966 --> 00:08:58,333
Make sure he doesn't fall.

201
00:08:58,333 --> 00:08:59,233
- Okay.
- It's downhill.

202
00:08:59,900 --> 00:09:00,733
There you go.
(Can you see me?)

203
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:03,866
That's right.

204
00:09:03,866 --> 00:09:05,100
There you go.

205
00:09:05,100 --> 00:09:06,400
(Climbing)

206
00:09:06,912 --> 00:09:07,746
We're here.

207
00:09:07,747 --> 00:09:08,825
(They even finished the stairs course.)

208
00:09:08,825 --> 00:09:10,333
Guys, hi.

209
00:09:10,333 --> 00:09:12,066
(It's a success!)

210
00:09:12,066 --> 00:09:12,900
Yu Jun.

211
00:09:15,500 --> 00:09:16,633
Shall we go see them again?

212
00:09:17,233 --> 00:09:19,266
(Going down by using HUENINGKAI
like a cable car)

213
00:09:19,266 --> 00:09:20,200
Did you take a tour?

214
00:09:20,600 --> 00:09:22,266
He ran away, so I caught him.

215
00:09:22,266 --> 00:09:24,800
(Getting off HUENINGKAI Cable Car)

216
00:09:25,233 --> 00:09:26,533
What? Does he want to go down?

217
00:09:26,533 --> 00:09:27,333
Does he?

218
00:09:27,333 --> 00:09:28,366
I think so.

219
00:09:28,366 --> 00:09:29,133
Do you want to go down?

220
00:09:30,500 --> 00:09:31,500
(Lying down)

221
00:09:31,500 --> 00:09:32,533
That's how he goes down?

222
00:09:32,666 --> 00:09:34,633
(Yu Jun, the Master of reversing)

223
00:09:34,633 --> 00:09:36,433
- Are you slime?
- He's good at it.

224
00:09:36,433 --> 00:09:38,166
- He went down well.
- Catch him.

225
00:09:38,166 --> 00:09:39,300
He's done that before.

226
00:09:40,233 --> 00:09:41,633
(Pushing the cart)

227
00:09:41,633 --> 00:09:44,800
(Following the cart)

228
00:09:46,733 --> 00:09:47,733
(Sitting down)

229
00:09:47,733 --> 00:09:49,166
He wanted to sit down and rest.

230
00:09:49,533 --> 00:09:51,433
(YEONJUN comes down slowly.)

231
00:09:51,433 --> 00:09:53,233
Let me lie on Yu Jun's knee.

232
00:09:53,233 --> 00:09:56,033
(The 320-month-old is bothering
the 15-month-old.)

233
00:09:56,033 --> 00:09:57,333
That looks funny.

234
00:09:57,633 --> 00:09:59,533
Yu Jun, stroke my hair.

235
00:09:59,533 --> 00:10:00,733
(Go away.)

236
00:10:00,834 --> 00:10:02,668
(YEONJUN is going
for the cushy knee again.)

237
00:10:03,169 --> 00:10:04,202
Pat, pat.

238
00:10:04,203 --> 00:10:04,903
(That tickles!)

239
00:10:04,904 --> 00:10:07,272
(Go away!)

240
00:10:07,574 --> 00:10:10,576
He left, thinking, "I wanted to rest.
Stop bothering me!"

241
00:10:10,577 --> 00:10:11,644
He doesn't care.

242
00:10:11,645 --> 00:10:13,512
(I love this cart!)

243
00:10:14,214 --> 00:10:15,681
(Let's go!)

244
00:10:15,682 --> 00:10:18,751
(The key chain he got earlier)

245
00:10:19,419 --> 00:10:21,387
(Walking with his big key chain guy
by his side)

246
00:10:21,388 --> 00:10:23,055
(So happy)

247
00:10:23,056 --> 00:10:24,456
(After the tour)

248
00:10:24,457 --> 00:10:25,891
(Parking the cart)

249
00:10:25,892 --> 00:10:27,627
All that walking,
and you want to come back to me, right?

250
00:10:28,428 --> 00:10:29,528
I knew it.

251
00:10:31,331 --> 00:10:32,264
Lie down.

252
00:10:32,599 --> 00:10:34,934
- He's telling you to lie down.
- No, he just wanted to sit.

253
00:10:35,402 --> 00:10:37,236
"What's wrong with this guy?"

254
00:10:37,237 --> 00:10:38,188
(YEONJUN enjoying it regardless)

255
00:10:38,271 --> 00:10:39,105
"Stop it!"

256
00:10:39,106 --> 00:10:40,606
(My gosh, you scared me!)

257
00:10:40,607 --> 00:10:42,608
(Yu Jun is slowly inching away.)

258
00:10:42,609 --> 00:10:44,777
(Hang out with me!)

259
00:10:44,778 --> 00:10:46,779
(What a weird uncle.)

260
00:10:46,780 --> 00:10:47,880
(Crawling to Yu Jun)

261
00:10:47,881 --> 00:10:48,848
Here.

262
00:10:49,883 --> 00:10:52,651
(I'm here to get you, Yu Jun!)

263
00:10:53,887 --> 00:10:56,322
(Yu Jun is diving
into HUENINGKAI's arms, startled.)

264
00:10:57,057 --> 00:10:58,024
Did I scare you?

265
00:10:58,025 --> 00:10:59,759
- Did he get scared?
- But he smiled.

266
00:10:59,760 --> 00:11:01,327
- Did he?
- He smiled.

267
00:11:01,328 --> 00:11:02,928
- Really?
- He smiled when he ran away.

268
00:11:03,329 --> 00:11:07,499
(Shall I chase him again, then?)

269
00:11:08,168 --> 00:11:09,869
- He loves me!
- He smiled.

270
00:11:09,870 --> 00:11:10,836
(He arrived in no time.)

271
00:11:11,271 --> 00:11:12,338
(It's a beast! I have to hide!)

272
00:11:12,339 --> 00:11:13,772
He's having fun.

273
00:11:16,042 --> 00:11:17,042
Take this, Yu Jun!

274
00:11:18,078 --> 00:11:20,312
I love your chubby legs.

275
00:11:20,313 --> 00:11:22,114
They're seriously the best.
They're so plump.

276
00:11:22,115 --> 00:11:23,149
How can his legs be so cushy?

277
00:11:23,283 --> 00:11:24,616
Welcome to Mozzarella Land!

278
00:11:25,552 --> 00:11:26,986
- Yes!
- Yes!

279
00:11:26,987 --> 00:11:28,587
- Put your hands up!
- Put your hands in the air!

280
00:11:29,189 --> 00:11:29,922
(Humph!)

281
00:11:29,923 --> 00:11:31,390
- He wants to be left alone.
- He does.

282
00:11:31,391 --> 00:11:32,491
Let's leave him.

283
00:11:32,492 --> 00:11:33,459
Let's do that.

284
00:11:33,460 --> 00:11:35,394
(He's taking a weird pose.)

285
00:11:35,395 --> 00:11:36,428
Is he pooping?

286
00:11:36,596 --> 00:11:37,496
Did you just poop?

287
00:11:38,231 --> 00:11:39,164
He pooped, right?

288
00:11:39,165 --> 00:11:41,567
I know what this is about.
You know how you want to be alone...

289
00:11:41,568 --> 00:11:42,668
when you go to the bathroom?

290
00:11:42,669 --> 00:11:43,335
(Exactly!)

291
00:11:43,336 --> 00:11:44,836
He keeps squatting and doing this.

292
00:11:45,538 --> 00:11:46,571
- Yu Jun.
- He keeps doing this.

293
00:11:47,107 --> 00:11:48,708
(Like this, Uncle?)

294
00:11:48,709 --> 00:11:51,077
- He definitely pooped just now.
- My goodness!

295
00:11:51,078 --> 00:11:53,413
- He just pooped.
- He definitely did.

296
00:11:53,414 --> 00:11:54,613
Take all your team rings off.

297
00:11:55,081 --> 00:11:56,715
(Always ready for emergencies)

298
00:11:56,716 --> 00:11:57,582
Oh, gosh.

299
00:11:57,917 --> 00:11:59,718
Yu Jun, stop rubbing your poop
all over your diaper.

300
00:12:01,454 --> 00:12:02,888
Try feeling it.

301
00:12:03,857 --> 00:12:05,024
Can you stay still for a moment?

302
00:12:05,025 --> 00:12:06,692
(Yu Jun is suddenly obsessed
with walking forward.)

303
00:12:06,693 --> 00:12:07,726
He definitely pooped.

304
00:12:08,194 --> 00:12:09,170
Wait!

305
00:12:09,195 --> 00:12:10,562
He definitely pooped.

306
00:12:10,563 --> 00:12:12,030
(Sniffing him)

307
00:12:12,432 --> 00:12:13,198
I don't smell it, though.

308
00:12:13,199 --> 00:12:15,368
He doesn't stink,
but we should still check.

309
00:12:15,668 --> 00:12:17,202
- He didn't poop.
- No, he didn't.

310
00:12:17,203 --> 00:12:19,537
- Nice!
- Nice.

311
00:12:20,240 --> 00:12:22,241
(Uncle?)

312
00:12:23,276 --> 00:12:24,409
Yu Jun, nice!

313
00:12:24,911 --> 00:12:26,211
Yu Jun, nice!

314
00:12:26,412 --> 00:12:28,680
(Nice!)

315
00:12:29,149 --> 00:12:30,416
He's so confused.

316
00:12:31,050 --> 00:12:32,617
Yu Jun, let's eat.

317
00:12:32,618 --> 00:12:34,353
Why don't we eat there?
It's more comfortable.

318
00:12:34,354 --> 00:12:35,420
Yu Jun!

319
00:12:35,755 --> 00:12:37,589
What's this? Yu Jun, what is this?

320
00:12:37,590 --> 00:12:38,890
Why is your belly already so big?

321
00:12:38,891 --> 00:12:40,058
You're HUENINGKAI.

322
00:12:40,426 --> 00:12:42,394
- You're HUENINGKAI.
- You're just like me!

323
00:12:42,529 --> 00:12:44,363
- Let's eat.
- Let's eat!

324
00:12:44,864 --> 00:12:45,697
Come here.

325
00:12:46,599 --> 00:12:47,599
Tofu.

326
00:12:48,601 --> 00:12:49,734
(Tofu for an appetizer)

327
00:12:49,735 --> 00:12:52,103
- Good boy!
- It's good, isn't it?

328
00:12:53,506 --> 00:12:54,873
- Do you like it?
- Do you?

329
00:12:55,408 --> 00:12:57,843
(Waiting for some more
with his tiny mouth)

330
00:12:58,111 --> 00:12:59,578
Good boy!

331
00:13:00,180 --> 00:13:01,046
Is it good?

332
00:13:01,047 --> 00:13:02,214
"Yes, it is!"

333
00:13:02,615 --> 00:13:04,182
- "So yummy!"
- "So yummy!"

334
00:13:05,552 --> 00:13:08,120
Let's give him three more spoonfuls
of the tofu.

335
00:13:08,655 --> 00:13:11,423
Just three more.
He has to eat his baby food soon.

336
00:13:13,293 --> 00:13:14,260
He loves it.
(Three spoons aren't enough.)

337
00:13:15,929 --> 00:13:17,329
(Give me more already!)

338
00:13:17,330 --> 00:13:18,364
You're so happy.

339
00:13:18,498 --> 00:13:20,632
You're so popular, Yu Jun.

340
00:13:21,000 --> 00:13:21,866
He's so excited.

341
00:13:21,867 --> 00:13:23,501
(Look at me doing the moonwalk
after having tofu!)

342
00:13:24,871 --> 00:13:25,771
He's learned a new skill.

343
00:13:25,772 --> 00:13:27,139
(Give me some!)

344
00:13:27,273 --> 00:13:28,139
Open up.

345
00:13:28,541 --> 00:13:29,608
You like it!

346
00:13:29,609 --> 00:13:31,112
(It's rare to see a baby
with such a big appetite.)

347
00:13:31,137 --> 00:13:32,237
Good boy!

348
00:13:32,979 --> 00:13:34,580
Why do you keep backing up?

349
00:13:36,216 --> 00:13:36,982
(For more tofu!)

350
00:13:36,983 --> 00:13:39,185
- Okay.
- Walking backward is good for you.

351
00:13:39,186 --> 00:13:39,985
Yes.

352
00:13:40,155 --> 00:13:42,054
(So yummy)

353
00:13:42,322 --> 00:13:44,323
(Taking big steps after some tofu)

354
00:13:44,324 --> 00:13:45,925
Okay.

355
00:13:45,926 --> 00:13:47,693
He asks for more after five steps.

356
00:13:48,394 --> 00:13:50,195
- So cute.
- I guess he loves it.

357
00:13:50,530 --> 00:13:51,730
He's about to finish the whole thing.

358
00:13:51,731 --> 00:13:52,998
He loves it.

359
00:13:52,999 --> 00:13:54,733
I don't even eat this much tofu.

360
00:13:56,102 --> 00:13:58,837
(Watching him having his feast)

361
00:13:59,205 --> 00:14:01,206
(Growing a tofu beard)

362
00:14:01,207 --> 00:14:03,241
(So yummy!)

363
00:14:03,242 --> 00:14:04,242
(I love it!)

364
00:14:04,243 --> 00:14:04,977
(Give me some more.)

365
00:14:04,978 --> 00:14:06,244
(That's the biggest
mouth on Yu Jun so far.)

366
00:14:06,245 --> 00:14:07,179
Why does he love it so much?
It must be really good.

367
00:14:08,314 --> 00:14:09,682
It's time for some baby food.

368
00:14:10,183 --> 00:14:12,117
(YEONJUN is preparing the main dish.)

369
00:14:12,685 --> 00:14:13,418
Yu Jun.

370
00:14:13,419 --> 00:14:15,186
(Yu Jun is going right to his food.)

371
00:14:15,187 --> 00:14:16,855
Here's your meal!

372
00:14:17,490 --> 00:14:19,591
You got tofu all over me.

373
00:14:21,661 --> 00:14:22,761
Just a second.

374
00:14:23,463 --> 00:14:26,699
(Waiting for his main)

375
00:14:26,700 --> 00:14:28,233
(Give it to me already!)

376
00:14:28,468 --> 00:14:29,635
Look at him with his mouth open.

377
00:14:29,802 --> 00:14:30,735
He's so cute.
Good boy!

378
00:14:31,504 --> 00:14:32,470
(Om nom)

379
00:14:32,672 --> 00:14:33,672
(I'm so excited!)

380
00:14:33,673 --> 00:14:35,040
(This is the best!)

381
00:14:35,375 --> 00:14:36,442
Are you happy?

382
00:14:37,543 --> 00:14:38,543
He's such a good boy.

383
00:14:38,845 --> 00:14:39,678
Open up!

384
00:14:41,114 --> 00:14:43,782
We have to take that away from him,
but I feel like he'll cry if we do.

385
00:14:44,150 --> 00:14:46,051
- Yummy!
- Yummy!

386
00:14:46,186 --> 00:14:46,985
Yummy!

387
00:14:47,353 --> 00:14:49,754
(Yu Jun couldn't be happier.)

388
00:14:50,423 --> 00:14:52,991
Good boy! You're eating so well!

389
00:14:52,992 --> 00:14:53,825
(Proud of his big appetite)

390
00:14:55,261 --> 00:14:57,295
- Good boy!
- You're so good!

391
00:14:58,164 --> 00:14:59,965
- My big belly monster loves his food!
- Are you done?

392
00:14:59,966 --> 00:15:01,299
(No!)

393
00:15:02,001 --> 00:15:03,501
- Good boy!
- There we go!

394
00:15:03,936 --> 00:15:05,904
(I'm so happy.)

395
00:15:06,539 --> 00:15:08,073
Do you want to mix that with this?

396
00:15:09,008 --> 00:15:10,909
How are you going to eat it?

397
00:15:11,878 --> 00:15:12,778
Here you go.

398
00:15:12,779 --> 00:15:14,079
(Food delivery service for Yu Jun)

399
00:15:14,080 --> 00:15:15,247
Open up!

400
00:15:16,115 --> 00:15:17,549
There's my good boy!

401
00:15:18,551 --> 00:15:19,618
Yu Jun!

402
00:15:19,886 --> 00:15:21,486
You're getting food all over me!

403
00:15:22,021 --> 00:15:22,854
Hey!

404
00:15:23,990 --> 00:15:25,357
You really love to eat!

405
00:15:26,659 --> 00:15:27,491
He's done.

406
00:15:27,492 --> 00:15:29,427
- He's done. Let's wash this.
- This.

407
00:15:30,430 --> 00:15:31,563
Do we have a clean bib?

408
00:15:33,032 --> 00:15:34,966
- Yummy!
- You...

409
00:15:34,967 --> 00:15:36,134
(A new monster uncle)

410
00:15:36,135 --> 00:15:38,136
You're a beast!

411
00:15:38,871 --> 00:15:39,738
It's a bit small.

412
00:15:39,739 --> 00:15:41,740
(Babies turn into beasts
after a good meal.)

413
00:15:41,741 --> 00:15:42,874
It's too tight around his neck.

414
00:15:44,010 --> 00:15:45,277
Is it supposed to be like that?

415
00:15:45,278 --> 00:15:46,445
(You can't move now, sir.)

416
00:15:46,446 --> 00:15:47,279
- Hold on.
- Let's see.

417
00:15:48,047 --> 00:15:49,414
Check his bum.

418
00:15:49,415 --> 00:15:50,749
Just check inside the diaper.

419
00:15:50,750 --> 00:15:51,818
(Another diaper check after eating)

420
00:15:53,920 --> 00:15:57,623
(The baby is walking,
but the grown-up is crawling.)

421
00:15:57,624 --> 00:15:59,491
(The baby on the run has been arrested.)

422
00:15:59,492 --> 00:16:00,526
My little tadpole!

423
00:16:01,127 --> 00:16:02,494
Do you want to go up, Yu Jun?

424
00:16:02,495 --> 00:16:04,629
(That was a great meal.)

425
00:16:04,964 --> 00:16:07,799
(The live for "Show! Music Core"
has begun.)

426
00:16:07,800 --> 00:16:09,167
I'm DOHOON!

427
00:16:09,168 --> 00:16:11,470
(Yu Jun and TXT are back
in the green room.)

428
00:16:11,571 --> 00:16:14,406
(The uncles are getting ready
for the live performance.)

429
00:16:14,407 --> 00:16:16,808
(Yu Jun is filming his own show.)

430
00:16:16,919 --> 00:16:18,076
(A screen full of squishy cheeks)

431
00:16:18,077 --> 00:16:18,944
Is it good?

432
00:16:19,278 --> 00:16:22,213
(It's a silent show,
as he can't talk yet.)

433
00:16:22,715 --> 00:16:26,551
(It may be silent,
but it's still full of cuteness.)

434
00:16:27,220 --> 00:16:30,222
(Adjusting the camera for a moment)

435
00:16:30,490 --> 00:16:31,957
(Peeking)

436
00:16:32,959 --> 00:16:34,860
(Are you joining me?)

437
00:16:35,528 --> 00:16:37,062
(The baby dumpling
and the angelic HUENINGKAI)

438
00:16:37,063 --> 00:16:38,163
Look at you.

439
00:16:39,399 --> 00:16:41,333
You already know how to take a selfie?

440
00:16:41,334 --> 00:16:44,403
(His squishy cheeks and tiny mouth
with the handsome uncle are perfection.)

441
00:16:46,873 --> 00:16:48,006
The guys have passed out.

442
00:16:48,640 --> 00:16:49,535
(Uncle SOOBIN has passed out.)

443
00:16:49,536 --> 00:16:52,220
Yu Jun, those guys sleep more than you do.

444
00:16:52,912 --> 00:16:55,514
(Meanwhile, the 15-month-old seems to have
unlimited energy.)

445
00:16:55,515 --> 00:16:57,482
(So energetic)

446
00:16:58,718 --> 00:17:02,254
(We'll take a quick break.)

447
00:17:03,962 --> 00:17:04,958
(Let's head out.)
Okay.

448
00:17:08,094 --> 00:17:11,096
(The dumpling is going
on a hallway tour again.)

449
00:17:11,097 --> 00:17:12,130
Yu Jun!

450
00:17:12,432 --> 00:17:14,466
I'm back! Hug me.

451
00:17:14,867 --> 00:17:17,669
Hug me!

452
00:17:18,537 --> 00:17:19,504
He doesn't want a hug.

453
00:17:20,239 --> 00:17:22,207
Hug me!

454
00:17:22,442 --> 00:17:23,409
He doesn't want it.

455
00:17:24,511 --> 00:17:25,511
Yu Jun!

456
00:17:26,746 --> 00:17:28,547
You have to hug me. I'm back!

457
00:17:29,515 --> 00:17:30,815
(Turning away coldly)

458
00:17:30,816 --> 00:17:32,183
I missed you.

459
00:17:32,618 --> 00:17:33,618
Yu Jun!

460
00:17:33,619 --> 00:17:36,955
(The baby dumpling just wants to continue
his tour.)

461
00:17:37,356 --> 00:17:39,190
- Hello!
- Whatever! I'm kidnapping you!

462
00:17:39,759 --> 00:17:42,327
(How kind of the obsessive fan
to announce the kidnapping.)

463
00:17:42,328 --> 00:17:44,062
- Mommy!
- I'm sorry.

464
00:17:44,997 --> 00:17:47,732
(I have to get back on my tour.)

465
00:17:48,301 --> 00:17:51,103
(Do you love me that much?)

466
00:17:52,205 --> 00:17:55,974
(YEONJUN has become Yu Jun's private jet.)

467
00:17:55,977 --> 00:17:57,976
Show everyone how cute you are.

468
00:17:59,879 --> 00:18:02,180
(Like this?)

469
00:18:02,381 --> 00:18:05,850
(He's having a blast
turning the fan on and off.)

470
00:18:06,819 --> 00:18:07,786
Tell them you love them!

471
00:18:09,722 --> 00:18:10,622
Say, "I love you!"

472
00:18:10,623 --> 00:18:13,292
(No, let me show you how I look
with the fan instead.)

473
00:18:13,293 --> 00:18:14,225
Say, "I love you!"

474
00:18:14,226 --> 00:18:16,828
(Whatever. I'm just chilling here.)

475
00:18:16,829 --> 00:18:17,796
He's tired.

476
00:18:18,331 --> 00:18:20,332
(Getting tired)

477
00:18:20,600 --> 00:18:23,669
(He signed up to be a private jet,
but he's getting tired.)

478
00:18:23,870 --> 00:18:25,871
- This is the perfect bicep workout.
- Yes.

479
00:18:26,205 --> 00:18:29,507
(Overcome it with love!)

480
00:18:29,909 --> 00:18:33,812
(Re-energized after looking
at Yu Jun's face)

481
00:18:34,013 --> 00:18:37,282
(The obsessive fan is happy,
even though his arms are getting sore.)

482
00:18:38,251 --> 00:18:41,553
(This is paradise.)

483
00:18:42,121 --> 00:18:45,690
(Doing a dance challenge
while they're by the famous red wall)

484
00:18:46,058 --> 00:18:48,960
(The world's first K-pop dance challenge
with a baby in their arms)

485
00:18:48,961 --> 00:18:49,894
You're so good!

486
00:18:50,930 --> 00:18:54,466
(Yu Jun is enjoying it,)

487
00:18:54,467 --> 00:18:57,769
(and the fans will enjoy it too.)

488
00:18:57,871 --> 00:18:59,971
Yu Jun, is this a dream?

489
00:19:00,172 --> 00:19:03,174
(YEONJUN is more excited than Yu Jun.)

490
00:19:04,210 --> 00:19:06,711
(While they're having fun
doing the dance challenge)

491
00:19:07,947 --> 00:19:09,047
Say hello!

492
00:19:09,048 --> 00:19:10,615
(KISS OF LIFE is passing by
after their performance.)

493
00:19:10,616 --> 00:19:11,783
Say hi.

494
00:19:11,918 --> 00:19:14,653
(Grinning from ear to ear
after spotting Yu Jun)

495
00:19:15,288 --> 00:19:17,489
- Say hi.
- Hi!

496
00:19:17,490 --> 00:19:19,157
- Hello.
- Hi.

497
00:19:19,825 --> 00:19:20,825
Are you scared?

498
00:19:22,061 --> 00:19:24,363
(Checking his face)

499
00:19:24,364 --> 00:19:25,864
Hello!

500
00:19:25,865 --> 00:19:27,532
- Hello.
- Hi!

501
00:19:27,533 --> 00:19:28,667
He's so cute, right?

502
00:19:29,091 --> 00:19:30,559
They're big brothers!

503
00:19:30,560 --> 00:19:31,469
(Yu Jun is as popular as Uncles.)

504
00:19:31,470 --> 00:19:33,204
- Hello!
- Hello!

505
00:19:33,664 --> 00:19:34,539
Hello.

506
00:19:34,840 --> 00:19:36,240
Can you feel it, Yu Jun?

507
00:19:36,376 --> 00:19:37,375
You're so popular.

508
00:19:38,077 --> 00:19:39,744
Do you know how popular you are?

509
00:19:39,745 --> 00:19:41,246
(The little prince of "Show! Music Core")

510
00:19:41,380 --> 00:19:42,814
(Then the fan meeting continues.)

511
00:19:42,815 --> 00:19:44,048
- Hello.
- Hello.

512
00:19:44,049 --> 00:19:46,351
- Hello.
- How are you?

513
00:19:46,953 --> 00:19:48,320
- Hello.
- We're here to see Yu Jun.

514
00:19:48,854 --> 00:19:50,655
(The fan meet-and-greet continues
in the green room.)

515
00:19:50,656 --> 00:19:53,692
You have the smallest age gap with Yu Jun,

516
00:19:53,693 --> 00:19:54,759
so try talking to him.

517
00:19:54,760 --> 00:19:56,928
(A teenager with a 15-month-old)

518
00:19:56,929 --> 00:19:58,963
- I'm JAMES.
- JAMES.

519
00:19:58,964 --> 00:20:00,966
- It's JAMES!
- He won't even look at me.

520
00:20:00,966 --> 00:20:01,999
JAMES.

521
00:20:01,999 --> 00:20:03,699
(Feeling shy
by the sudden one-on-one fan meeting)

522
00:20:03,866 --> 00:20:04,866
Say hi.

523
00:20:05,233 --> 00:20:06,533
(Giving a bow)

524
00:20:07,933 --> 00:20:10,266
(Guys fall for him after one greeting.)

525
00:20:10,266 --> 00:20:11,266
He's got swag.

526
00:20:11,266 --> 00:20:13,833
(Confused)

527
00:20:14,133 --> 00:20:17,133
He must be comfortable around older guys.

528
00:20:18,399 --> 00:20:19,699
He's okay.

529
00:20:19,699 --> 00:20:20,733
(Touching on their first meeting)

530
00:20:20,733 --> 00:20:22,099
- Handshake.
- Handshake.

531
00:20:22,099 --> 00:20:23,966
(This isn't right.)

532
00:20:24,166 --> 00:20:26,433
(Getting out)

533
00:20:26,433 --> 00:20:28,366
(Cool as ever)

534
00:20:28,599 --> 00:20:30,466
- Does he talk?
- Not yet.

535
00:20:30,466 --> 00:20:31,499
He can only say, "Mom."

536
00:20:31,499 --> 00:20:32,499
"Mom."

537
00:20:33,033 --> 00:20:35,133
He's young,
but he already knows the camera.

538
00:20:35,699 --> 00:20:38,133
- Don't you think he's handsome?
- Yes, he's good-looking.

539
00:20:38,133 --> 00:20:39,166
He's handsome.

540
00:20:39,166 --> 00:20:40,733
(Thank you.)

541
00:20:40,733 --> 00:20:41,966
- All right.
- His second greeting.

542
00:20:42,366 --> 00:20:45,433
- Can you pronounce "REDRED?"
- Do you want to say "REDRED?"

543
00:20:45,433 --> 00:20:48,166
(Members are excited.)

544
00:20:48,433 --> 00:20:50,333
(I'll do it after a year.)

545
00:20:50,799 --> 00:20:53,066
- He arranged it.
- Tidying up!

546
00:20:53,066 --> 00:20:54,266
He likes it when we clap.

547
00:20:55,066 --> 00:20:57,566
(So Yu Jun likes clapping?)

548
00:20:57,833 --> 00:20:59,499
- Let's go!
- Oh, the wet tissue?

549
00:20:59,733 --> 00:21:02,533
(Even though he just pulled out
a wet tissue...)

550
00:21:02,999 --> 00:21:05,566
(You're the best, Yu Jun!)

551
00:21:05,866 --> 00:21:07,533
(One more time?)

552
00:21:08,133 --> 00:21:09,966
(If Yu Jun is happy,)

553
00:21:09,966 --> 00:21:14,066
(so are we!)

554
00:21:14,266 --> 00:21:16,266
His hands are so tiny.

555
00:21:17,266 --> 00:21:18,666
(A gift for you.)

556
00:21:19,433 --> 00:21:20,466
He gives the one he used.

557
00:21:21,299 --> 00:21:22,299
Thank you.

558
00:21:22,799 --> 00:21:23,799
He gave you a gift.

559
00:21:23,799 --> 00:21:25,066
- A gift!
- He's wiping his hands.

560
00:21:25,066 --> 00:21:26,166
He's wiping them so hard.

561
00:21:26,899 --> 00:21:28,666
(SEONGHYEON is deeply honored.)

562
00:21:28,666 --> 00:21:29,666
Hand?

563
00:21:30,199 --> 00:21:31,199
Me too?

564
00:21:31,499 --> 00:21:34,199
(Feeling awesome)

565
00:21:34,933 --> 00:21:36,033
- What?
- What is it?

566
00:21:36,033 --> 00:21:38,666
(Showing off his cleaning skills
while he's at it)

567
00:21:38,933 --> 00:21:41,033
You guys are giving the best reactions.

568
00:21:41,033 --> 00:21:42,999
- Such a warm-hearted guy!
- You're so good!

569
00:21:42,999 --> 00:21:44,033
(Their reactions are "Green Green.")

570
00:21:44,166 --> 00:21:45,366
(Hyped up thanks to CORTIS)

571
00:21:45,366 --> 00:21:46,599
- Check those guys!
- Good boy.

572
00:21:46,799 --> 00:21:48,099
Good luck with your live show.

573
00:21:48,099 --> 00:21:50,099
- See you later.
- Good luck.

574
00:21:50,099 --> 00:21:52,333
- Goodbye.
- He's cool. I like it.

575
00:21:52,333 --> 00:21:53,399
(The fan meeting ends on a high note.)

576
00:21:53,599 --> 00:21:57,033
(And the live show is wrapping up.)

577
00:21:57,566 --> 00:21:59,333
- TXT, you're up.
- Okay.

578
00:21:59,333 --> 00:22:00,333
(Time to head down)
Let's go.

579
00:22:01,333 --> 00:22:03,066
You won't leave YEONJUN's side today.

580
00:22:03,799 --> 00:22:06,333
Even last time, I was tired
but kept holding him.

581
00:22:07,066 --> 00:22:08,066
So he can get used to me.

582
00:22:08,299 --> 00:22:09,699
Then he must like your arms.

583
00:22:10,199 --> 00:22:12,966
(A position earned through hard work)

584
00:22:14,699 --> 00:22:18,633
(Parenting and recharging Yu Jun
even right before the live show)

585
00:22:19,366 --> 00:22:21,133
(Staying by his side even backstage)

586
00:22:21,466 --> 00:22:24,133
(The fantastic YJ duo)

587
00:22:30,333 --> 00:22:33,633
(The YJs relax before the live show.)

588
00:22:33,999 --> 00:22:35,933
(Lose yourself to the rhythm.)

589
00:22:38,033 --> 00:22:40,299
(He can't hold back his excitement.)

590
00:22:40,699 --> 00:22:42,333
In 3, 2, 1, let's go!

591
00:22:42,633 --> 00:22:45,233
(I don't know him.)

592
00:22:45,599 --> 00:22:48,766
(Somebody stop this guy.)

593
00:22:48,766 --> 00:22:49,766
You're up.

594
00:22:50,033 --> 00:22:51,033
Time to go!

595
00:22:51,333 --> 00:22:52,499
We'll be right back, Yu Jun.

596
00:22:52,933 --> 00:22:54,066
Yu Jun, we're going now.

597
00:22:54,066 --> 00:22:57,433
(Saying goodbye to the uncles
for the second time)

598
00:22:58,466 --> 00:23:01,699
(Yu Jun doesn't cry this time
since it's his second goodbye.)

599
00:23:01,966 --> 00:23:04,966
(Good luck!)

600
00:23:06,299 --> 00:23:10,533
(Thanks to him, the uncles perform
without worrying.)

601
00:23:15,666 --> 00:23:19,333
(Watching the live show
in the waiting room)

602
00:23:22,899 --> 00:23:25,599
(After the performance and 30 seconds
before the ranking announcement)

603
00:23:25,766 --> 00:23:27,733
(TXT is the first-place nominee today.)

604
00:23:27,966 --> 00:23:31,033
(The members are extremely nervous.)

605
00:23:31,599 --> 00:23:33,099
("Show! Music Core"
starts the ranking announcement.)

606
00:23:33,099 --> 00:23:36,333
This is "Show! Music Core,"
and the live voting now closes.

607
00:23:36,333 --> 00:23:40,766
- In 5, 4, 3, 2, 1.
- In 5, 4, 3, 2, 1.

608
00:23:40,766 --> 00:23:42,699
- The live voting is now closed.
- The live voting is now closed.

609
00:23:43,033 --> 00:23:46,766
Who will win first place today?
Please show us the results.

610
00:23:49,766 --> 00:23:53,499
(Yu Jun is also nervous.)

611
00:23:55,266 --> 00:23:56,299
Please!

612
00:23:58,166 --> 00:23:59,966
- Let's do this.
- Let's do it!

613
00:24:00,733 --> 00:24:02,033
Let's win this!

614
00:24:04,299 --> 00:24:07,366
Lastly, let's check the final results
with the live votes included.

615
00:24:07,366 --> 00:24:08,399
Third place goes to...

616
00:24:09,266 --> 00:24:10,266
AKMU.

617
00:24:10,266 --> 00:24:11,433
And today's first place goes to...

618
00:24:11,966 --> 00:24:13,266
We did it!

619
00:24:13,266 --> 00:24:17,133
(TXT wins the first place
in Episode 943 of "Show! Music Core.")

620
00:24:17,133 --> 00:24:18,233
All right!

621
00:24:18,233 --> 00:24:20,766
(Their first win at this show
in eight years after debut)

622
00:24:21,266 --> 00:24:22,666
(Yes!)

623
00:24:24,933 --> 00:24:27,333
(The waiting room is
also filled with joy.)

624
00:24:27,333 --> 00:24:29,333
(Their first win in "Show! Music Core"
with Yu Jun)

625
00:24:29,333 --> 00:24:31,099
First place, Yu Jun!

626
00:24:31,899 --> 00:24:32,999
Thank you.

627
00:24:34,999 --> 00:24:36,733
(I'm so happy!)

628
00:24:40,599 --> 00:24:43,833
First, for MOA,
who gave us this precious award!

629
00:24:45,166 --> 00:24:47,133
Thank you so much.

630
00:24:47,133 --> 00:24:50,299
We know very well that winning an award
in our eighth year...

631
00:24:50,299 --> 00:24:51,799
shouldn't be taken for granted.

632
00:24:51,799 --> 00:24:55,033
We'll accept this award with gratitude.

633
00:24:55,033 --> 00:24:56,466
Thank you so much.

634
00:24:56,466 --> 00:24:58,633
- Thank you!
- Thank you!

635
00:24:58,633 --> 00:25:02,266
(Yu Jun turns into a wreath
to celebrate their first-place win.)

636
00:25:02,433 --> 00:25:03,466
It's our first time.

637
00:25:03,833 --> 00:25:05,099
- First time in "Show! Music Core."
- First time.

638
00:25:05,399 --> 00:25:06,433
- Our first win.
- It's our first award.

639
00:25:07,199 --> 00:25:10,066
(Leader SOOBIN tears up.)

640
00:25:11,533 --> 00:25:14,299
(Congratulations, Uncles.)

641
00:25:15,166 --> 00:25:18,233
(A first-place cake prepared for TXT)

642
00:25:18,233 --> 00:25:19,266
You shouldn't have!

643
00:25:19,799 --> 00:25:23,633
Guys, today is the 943rd episode
of "Show! Music Core."

644
00:25:23,899 --> 00:25:24,933
(The fateful win in Episode 943)

645
00:25:24,933 --> 00:25:27,233
On this special day,
for the first time in this show...

646
00:25:27,933 --> 00:25:29,599
(Yu Jun!)

647
00:25:31,833 --> 00:25:36,766
(Yu Jun can't miss the celebration party.)

648
00:25:37,933 --> 00:25:38,966
Yu Jun.

649
00:25:39,533 --> 00:25:41,366
- We won first place.
- We won!

650
00:25:44,466 --> 00:25:46,099
Yu Jun, high five!

651
00:25:47,633 --> 00:25:48,633
(A successful high five)

652
00:25:48,633 --> 00:25:49,666
So hot, right?

653
00:25:50,899 --> 00:25:53,366
- Thank you, MOA.
- Thank you.

654
00:25:54,099 --> 00:25:55,566
Isn't he so cute?

655
00:25:55,566 --> 00:25:57,033
- Yes!
- Yes!

656
00:25:58,466 --> 00:26:01,966
(TXT Daddies,
congratulations on your first-place win!)

657
00:26:02,166 --> 00:26:03,266
Say hi, Yu Jun.

658
00:26:03,266 --> 00:26:04,266
- Hello.
- Say hi.

659
00:26:04,266 --> 00:26:05,699
(A bow to celebrate their first place)

660
00:26:05,699 --> 00:26:06,799
Hello.

661
00:26:07,533 --> 00:26:10,266
We'll wrap up and take our leave.

662
00:26:10,266 --> 00:26:12,499
- This has been TOMORROW X TOGETHER!
- TOGETHER!

663
00:26:12,499 --> 00:26:13,833
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

664
00:26:14,399 --> 00:26:16,799
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

665
00:26:16,799 --> 00:26:19,599
- Thank you so much.
- Thank you.

666
00:26:20,599 --> 00:26:22,133
- Thank you.
- We love you, MOA!

667
00:26:23,199 --> 00:26:26,266
Goodbye.

668
00:26:26,266 --> 00:26:28,499
(With the tension gone,
their win finally feels real.)

669
00:26:28,499 --> 00:26:29,499
Good work, guys.

670
00:26:30,166 --> 00:26:31,299
Guys, congratulations.

671
00:26:31,299 --> 00:26:32,899
- Congratulations.
- We finally got it.

672
00:26:32,899 --> 00:26:34,433
Good work. We finally won.

673
00:26:34,433 --> 00:26:35,999
So this is what the trophy looks like.

674
00:26:35,999 --> 00:26:36,999
You got it right after joining us.

675
00:26:36,999 --> 00:26:39,699
Yu Jun, you wouldn't know
since you won right away,

676
00:26:39,699 --> 00:26:42,699
but we worked for eight years
to win this award.

677
00:26:43,066 --> 00:26:44,266
It's our first time in eight years.

678
00:26:44,266 --> 00:26:45,266
(Their lucky charm)

679
00:26:45,266 --> 00:26:48,233
(The cake looks so good.)

680
00:26:48,533 --> 00:26:50,633
- Help us get another win next time.
- Okay.

681
00:26:50,633 --> 00:26:52,133
- In 1, 2, 3.
- In 1, 2, 3.

682
00:26:52,833 --> 00:26:54,066
The cake looks so beautiful.

683
00:26:54,066 --> 00:26:57,799
- Thank you.
- Thank you!

684
00:26:58,299 --> 00:26:59,699
(The crew prepared their own cake
for celebration.)

685
00:26:59,699 --> 00:27:00,866
Thank you!

686
00:27:00,866 --> 00:27:01,933
This is beautiful!

687
00:27:02,333 --> 00:27:03,699
- Goodness.
- Thank you.

688
00:27:03,999 --> 00:27:06,166
- This feels amazing.
- Seriously.

689
00:27:06,999 --> 00:27:08,899
- Is this for real?
- I know.

690
00:27:09,533 --> 00:27:10,899
It wasn't an easy journey.

691
00:27:10,899 --> 00:27:13,433
- Good work. Congratulations.
- Congratulations.

692
00:27:13,433 --> 00:27:14,899
You worked hard too, Yu Jun.

693
00:27:15,899 --> 00:27:17,133
Yu Jun didn't work so hard.

694
00:27:17,433 --> 00:27:20,133
He did nothing
and still won first place right away!

695
00:27:20,133 --> 00:27:21,733
I'm so jealous of you.

696
00:27:21,733 --> 00:27:24,133
(Still, Yu Jun did his part
as a lucky charm.)

697
00:27:24,933 --> 00:27:27,499
I couldn't help but scream.
